No. 10, in page 10, line 7, at end insert— '(3A) Where the Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service proposes to revise a Code under this section, it shall transmit a draft of the revised Code to the Secretary of State who shall—
(a) if he approves of it, lay the draft before each House of Parliament;
(b) if he does not approve of it, publish details of his reasons for withholding approval.'.
